\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Comparison between the MINVO basis and the Bernstein basis for 
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

.
 The simplex found using the MINVO basis (left) encloses the 
\begin_inset Formula $3^{rd}$
\end_inset

-order polynomial curve in red, and, for any 
\begin_inset Formula $3^{rd}$
\end_inset

-order polynomial curve, the MINVO basis generates a simplex that is 
\begin_inset Formula $2.36$
\end_inset

 times smaller that the one found using the Bernstein basis (right).
 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Comparison3d"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

